    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Houses that are generally two-story, one-room deep, and which have a thin profile. Prominent in England, they became particularly popular in the American mid-Atlantic states from 1700-1915, and symbolized rural prosperity. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052033/Foster, American Houses (2004)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>通常為兩層樓高、縱深僅約一個房間長的房屋形式，外形高窄。原流行於英國境內，於西元 1700 至 1915 年間盛行於美國中大西洋岸各州，為鄉村興盛發展的象徵。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
